The paper discusses the development of a streaming data life cycle process for the Internet of Moving Things (IoMT) that incorporates an edge/fog/cloud architecture. This involves handling heterogeneous, streaming, and geographically-dispersed devices, which suggests that the paper could fall under the Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) category. The paper also discusses querying, aggregation, and analytics, which are topics that fall under Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Database (cs.DB) categories. Additionally, the paper discusses communication and process, which are topics that fall under Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) categories.
